  "body": "Moving trielog to the rockdb blob part\n\n* Can we delete the data stored in the rocksDB BlobDB as this is needed for pruning #5866? \n  * docs say yes, need to verify\n* From #5475 BlobDB is a better choice since it reduces a lot the write amplification during compaction, with the result of faster initial sync and less wear out of the disk\n* Verify if pruning has an impact on performance due to compaction #5866\n* We can't move the trie branches only the trie logs\n* Test that we can upgrade to a next Besu version\n* Test that we can downgrade to a previous Besu version\n* Should we have a feature flag for this or should it be enabled by default?\n\nNotes:\n* https://github.com/facebook/rocksdb/wiki/BlobDB\n* https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/5471\n* https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/5475",
